obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3952)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3952&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Environment`
  line `(Protection) Act, 1986.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and for`
  line `different areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 . 19th November, 1986, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1198(E), dated 12th November, 1986, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3953)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3953&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "environment" includes water, air and land and the inter-relationship which exists among and`
  line `between water, air and land, and human beings, other living creatures, plants, micro-organism and`
  line property;
  line
  line `(b) "environmental pollutant" means any solid, liquid or gaseous substance present in such`
  line `concentration as may be, or tend to be, injurious to environment;`
  line
  line `(c) " environmental pollution" means the presence in the environment of any environmental`
  line pollutant;
  line
  line `^1[(ca) "Fund" means the Environmental Protection Fund established under section 16;]`
  line
  line `(d) "handling", in relation to any substance, means the manufacture, processing, treatment,`
  line `package, storage, transportation, use, collection, destruction, conversion, offering for sale, transfer or`
  line `the like of such substance;`
  line
  line `(e) "hazardous substance" means any substance or preparation which, by reason of its chemical or`
  line `physico-chemical properties or handling, is liable to cause harm to human beings, other living`
  line `creatures, plants, micro-organism, property or the environment;`
  line
  line `(f) "occupier", in relation to any factory or premises, means a person who has control over the`
  line `affairs of the factory or the premises and includes, in relation to any substance, the person in`
  line `possession of the substance;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3954)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of Central Government to take measures to protect and improve environment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3954&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government shall have the power to`
  line `take all such measures as it deems necessary or expedient for the purpose of protecting and improving the`
  line `quality of the environment and preventing, controlling and abating environmental pollution.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), such`
  line `measures may include measures with respect to all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) co-ordination of actions by the State Governments, officers and other authorities--`
  line
  line `(a) under this Act, or the rules made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) under any other law for the time being in force which is relatable to the objects of this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(ii) planning and execution of a nation-wide programme for the prevention, control and`
  line `abatement of environmental pollution;`
  line
  line `(iii) laying down standards for the quality of environment in its various aspects;`
  line
  line `(iv) laying down standards for emission or discharge of environmental pollutants from various`
  line `sources whatsoever:`
  line
  line `Provided that different standards for emission or discharge may be laid down under this clause`
  line `from different sources having regard to the quality or composition of the emission or discharge of`
  line `environmental pollutants from such sources;`
  line
  line `(v) restriction of areas in which any industries, operations or processes or class of industries,`
  line `operations or processes shall not be carried out or shall be carried out subject to certain safeguards;`
  line
  line `(vi) laying down procedures and safeguards for the prevention of accidents which may cause`
  line `environmental pollution and remedial measures for such accidents;`
  line
  line `(vii) laying down procedures and safeguards for the handling of hazardous substances;`
  line
  line `(viii) examination of such manufacturing processes, materials and substances as are likely to`
  line `cause environmental pollution;`
  line
  line `(ix) carrying out and sponsoring investigations and research relating to problems of`
  line `environmental pollution;`
  line
  line `(x) inspection of any premises, plant, equipment, machinery, manufacturing or other processes,`
  line `materials or substances and giving, by order, of such directions to such authorities, officers or persons`
  line `as it may consider necessary to take steps for the prevention, control and abatement of environmental`
  line pollution;
  line
  line `(xi) establishment or recognition of environmental laboratories and institutes to carry out the`
  line `functions entrusted to such environmental laboratories and institutes under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xii) collection and dissemination of information in respect of matters relating to environmental`
  line pollution;
  line
  line `(xiii) preparation of manuals, codes or guides relating to the prevention, control and abatement of`
  line `environmental pollution;`
  line
  line `(xiv) such other matters as the Central Government deems necessary or expedient for the purpose`
  line `of securing the effective implementation of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, by order, published in the Official Gazette, constitute an authority or authorities by such name or`
  line `names as may be specified in the order for the purpose of exercising and performing such of the powers`
  line `and functions (including the power to issue directions under section 5) of the Central Government under`
  line `this Act and for taking measures with respect to such of the matters referred to in sub-section (2) as may`
  line `be mentioned in the order and subject to the supervision and control of the Central Government and the`
  line `provisions of such order, such authority or authorities may exercise the powers or perform the functions`
  line `or take the measures so mentioned in the order as if such authority or authorities had been empowered by`
  line `this Act to exercise those powers or perform those functions or take such measures.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3955)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of officers and their powers and functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3955&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (3) of section 3, the Central Government may appoint officers with such`
  line `designations as it thinks fit for the purposes of this Act and may entrust to them such of the powers and`
  line `functions under this Act as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers appointed under sub-section (1) shall be subject to the general control and direction`
  line `of the Central Government or, if so directed by that Government, also of the authority or authorities, if`
  line `any, constituted under sub-section (3) of section 3 or of any other authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3956)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3956&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law but subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Central Government may, in the exercise of its powers and performance of its`
  line `functions under this Act, issue directions in writing to any person, officer or any authority and such`
  line `person, officer or authority shall be bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the avoidance of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power to issue directions`
  line `under this section includes the power to direct--`
  line
  line `(a) the closure, prohibition or regulation of any industry, operation or process; or`
  line
  line `(b) stoppage or regulation of the supply of electricity or water or any other service.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (57336)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Appeal to National Green Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 2010, s. 36 and Schedule III (w.e.f. 18-10-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=57336&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line ^1[
  line `5A. Appeal to National Green Tribunal.—Any person aggrieved by any directions issues under`
  line `section 5, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010, may file an appeal to`
  line `the National Green Tribunal established under section 3 of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010, in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3957)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Rules to regulate environmental pollution.`
