  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3957&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make rules in respect of all or any of the matters referred to in section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the standards of quality of air, water or soil for various areas and purposes;`
  line
  line `(b) the maximum allowable limits of concentration of various environmental pollutants (including`
  line `noise) for different areas;`
  line
  line `(c) the procedures and safeguards for the handling of hazardous substances;`
  line
  line `(d) the prohibition and restrictions on the handling of hazardous substances in different areas;`
  line
  line `(e) the prohibition and restrictions on the location of industries and the carrying on of processes`
  line `and operations in different areas;`
  line
  line `(f) the procedures and safeguards for the prevention of accidents which may cause environmental`
  line `pollution and for providing for remedial measures for such accidents.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3958)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Persons carrying on industry, operations, etc., not to allow emission or discharge of environmental pollutants in excess of the standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3958&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No person carrying on any industry, operation`
  line `or process shall discharge or emit or permit to be discharged or emitted any environmental pollutant in`
  line `excess or such standards as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3959)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Persons handling hazardous substances to comply with procedural safeguards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3959&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No person`
  line `shall handle or cause to be handled any hazardous substance except in accordance with such procedure`
  line `and after complying with such safeguards as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3960)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Furnishing of information to authorities and agencies in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3960&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `discharge of any environmental pollutant in excess of the prescribed standards occurs or is apprehended`
  line `to occur due to any accident or other unforeseen act or event, the person responsible for such discharge`
  line `and the person in charge of the place at which such discharge occurs or is apprehended to occur shall be`
  line `bound to prevent or mitigate the environmental pollution caused as a result of such discharge and shall`
  line `also forthwith--`
  line
  line `(a) intimate the fact of such occurrence or apprehension of such occurrence; and`
  line
  line `(b) be bound, if called upon, to render all assistance,`
  line
  line `to such authorities or agencies as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of information with respect to the fact or apprehension of any occurrence of the nature`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1), whether through intimation under that sub-section or otherwise, the`
  line `authorities or agencies referred to in sub-section (1) shall, as early as practicable, cause such remedial`
  line `measures to be taken as are necessary to prevent or mitigate the environmental pollution.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses, if any, incurred by any authority or agency with respect to the remedial measures`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2), together with interest (at such reasonable rate as the Government may, by`
  line `order, fix) from the date when a demand for the expenses is made until it is paid, may be recovered by`
  line `such authority or agency from the person concerned as arrears of land revenue or of public demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3961)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Powers of entry and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sub-sections (2) to (4) (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3961&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, any person`
  line `empowered by the Central Government in this behalf shall have a right to enter, at all reasonable times`
  line `with such assistance as he considers necessary, any place--`
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of performing any of the functions of the Central Government entrusted to`
  line him;
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of determining whether and if so in what manner, any such functions are to be`
  line `performed or whether any provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder or any notice, order,`
  line `direction or authorisation served, made, given or granted under this Act is being or has been complied`
  line with;
  line
  line `(c) for the purpose of examining and testing any equipment, industrial plant, record, register,`
  line `document or any other material object or for conducting a search of any building in which he has`
  line `reason to believe that an offence under this Act or the rules made thereunder has been or is being or is`
  line `about to be committed and for seizing any such equipment, industrial plant, record, register,`
  line `document or other material object if he has reasons to believe that it may furnish evidence of the`
  line `commission of an offence punishable under this Act or the rules made thereunder or that such seizure`
  line `is necessary to prevent or mitigate environmental pollution.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Every person carrying on any industry, operation or process of handling any hazardous substance shall render assistance, as may be required, to the person empowered by the Central Government under sub-section (1) for carrying out the functions under that sub-section and if he fails to do so without any reasonable cause, he shall be liable to penalty provided under section 14B.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person willfully delays or obstructs any person empowered by the Central Government under sub-section (1) in the performance of his functions under sub-sections (1) or (2), he shall be liable to penalty provided under section 14B.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `to any search or seizures under this section as they apply to any search or seizures made under the`
  line `authority of a warrant issued under section 94 of that Code.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3962)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to take sample and procedure to be followed in connection therewith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3962&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government or any officer empowered by it in this behalf, shall have power to take, for the`
  line `purpose of analysis, samples of air, water, soil or other substance from any factory, premises or other`
  line `place in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The result of any analysis of a sample taken under sub-section (1) shall not be admissible in`
  line `evidence in any legal proceeding unless the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) are complied with.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), the person taking the sample under sub-section (1)`
  line shall,--
  line
  line `(a) serve on the occupier or his agent or person in charge of the place, a notice, then and there, in`
  line `such form as may be prescribed, of his intention to have it so analysed;`
  line
  line `(b) in the presence of the occupier or his agent or person, collect a sample for analysis;`
  line
  line `(c) cause the sample to be placed in a container or containers which shall be marked and sealed`
  line `and shall also be signed both by the person taking the sample and the occupier or his agent or person;`
  line
  line `(d) send without delay, the container or the containers to the laboratory established or recognised`
  line `by the Central Government under section 12.`
  line
  line `(4) When a sample is taken for analysis under sub-section (1) and the person taking the sample serves`
  line `on the occupier or his agent or person, a notice under clause (a) of sub-section (3), then,--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where the occupier, his agent or person wilfully absents himself, the person taking`
  line `the sample shall collect the sample for analysis to be placed in a container or containers which shall`
  line `be marked and sealed and shall also be signed by the person taking the sample, and`
  line
  line `(b) in a case where the occupier or his agent or person present at the time of taking the sample`
  line `refuses to sign the marked and sealed container or containers of the sample as required under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (3), the marked and sealed container or containers shall be signed by the`
  line `person taking the samples,`
  line
  line `and the container or containers shall be sent without delay by the person taking the sample for analysis to`
  line `the laboratory established or recognised under section 12 and such person shall inform the Government`
  line `Analyst appointed or recognised under section 13 in writing, about the wilful absence of the occupier or`
  line `his agent or person, or, as the case may be, his refusal to sign the container or containers.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3963)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Environmental laboratories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3963&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line Gazette,--
  line
  line `(a) establish one or more environmental laboratories;`
  line
  line `(b) recognise one or more laboratories or institutes as environmental laboratories to carry out the`
  line `functions entrusted to an environmental laboratory under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules specifying`
  line
  line `(a) the functions of the environmental laboratory;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure for the submission to the said laboratory of samples of air, water, soil or other`
  line `substance for analysis or tests, the form of the laboratory report thereon and the fees payable for such`
  line report;
  line
  line `(c) such other matters as may be necessary or expedient to enable that laboratory to carry out its`
  line functions.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3964)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Government Analysts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3964&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `appoint or recognise such persons as it thinks fit and having the prescribed qualifications to be`
  line `Government Analysts for the purpose of analysis of samples of air, water, soil or other substance sent for`
  line `analysis to any environmental laboratory established or recognised under sub-section (1) of section 12.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3965)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Reports of Government Analysts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3965&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any document purporting to be a report signed by a`
  line `Government Analyst may be used as evidence of the facts stated therein in any proceeding under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (89172)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 16
  title `Penalty for contravention of section 7 or section 8.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89172&sectionno=14A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Penalty for contravention of section 7 or section 8.--(1) If any person, contravenes provisions of section 7 or section 8 or the rules made thereunder, he shall be liable to penalty in respect of each such contravention, which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person continues contravention under sub-section (1), he shall be liable to additional penalty of fifty thousand rupees for every day during which such contravention continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_b:
  sectionId (89173)
  sectionNo 14B
  orderNo 17
  title `Penalty for contravention of sections 9, 10 and 11.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89173&sectionno=14B&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_14_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[14B. Penalty for contravention of sections 9, 10 and 11.--(1) If any person contravenes or does not comply with the provisions of section 9, section 10 or section 11 or orders or directions issued under those sections, he shall be liable to penalty in respect of each such contravention which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees but which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person continues contravention under sub-section (1), he shall be liable to additional penalty of ten thousand rupees for every day during which such contravention continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3966)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title `Penalty for contravention of the provisions of the Act and the rules, orders and directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 15 to 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3966&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Penalty for contravention of provisions of Act, rules, orders and directions.--(1) Where any person contravenes or does not comply with any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made or orders or directions issued thereunder for which no penalty is provided, he shall be liable to penalty in respect of each such contravention which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees but which may extend to fifteen`
  line `lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person continues contravention under sub-section (1), he shall be liable to additional`
  line `penalty of ten thousand rupees for every day during which such contravention continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (89174)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 19
  title `Penalty for contravention by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 15 to 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89174&sectionno=15A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Penalty for contravention by companies.--(1) Where any company contravenes any of the provisions of this Act, the company shall be liable to penalty for each such contravention which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any company continues contravention under sub-section (1), the company shall be liable to additional penalty of one lakh rupees for every day during which such contravention continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (89175)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 20
  title `Penalty for contravention by Government Department.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 15 to 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89175&sectionno=15B&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[15B. Penalty for contravention by Government Department.--(1) Where contravention of any of the provision of this Act has been committed by any Department of the Central Government or the State Government, the Head of the Department shall be liable to penalty equal to one month of his basic salary:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not be liable for such contravention, if he proves that the contravention was`
  line `committed without his knowledge or instructions or that he exercised all due diligence to prevent such`
  line contravention
  line
  line `(2) Where any contravention under sub-section (1) is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any`
  line `officer, other than the Head of the Department, the officer shall be liable to penalty equal to one month of`
  line `his basic salary:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not be liable for the contravention, if he proves that he exercised all due`
  line `diligence to avoid such contravention.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_c:
  sectionId (89176)
  sectionNo 15C
  orderNo 21
  title `Adjudicating officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_c_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 15 to 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89176&sectionno=15C&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_15_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[15C. Adjudicating officer.--(1) The Central Government, for the purposes of determining the penalties under this Act, may appoint an officer not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India or a Secretary to the State Government to be the adjudicating officer, to hold an inquiry and to`
  line `impose penalty in the manner, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may appoint as many adjudicating officers as may be required.`
  line
  line `(2) The adjudicating officer may--`
  line
  line `(a) call upon any person alleged to have contravened or not complied with the provisions of this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder or having the knowledge of the facts and circumstances of the`
  line case;
  line
  line `(b) require such person to produce any record, register or other document in his possession or any`
  line `other document, which in the opinion of the adjudicating officer may be relevant to the subjectmatter.`
  line
  line `(3) The adjudicating officer shall, after giving the person a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter, and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person concerned has contravened or has not complied with the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, he may impose such penalty as he thinks fit in accordance with the provisions of sections 14A, 14B, 15, 15A or section 15B, as the case may`
  line be
  line
  line `(4) The adjudicating officer, while adjudicating the quantum of penalty under sub-section (3), shall`
  line `have due regard to the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the population and the area impacted or affected due to such contravention or noncompliance;`
  line
  line `(b) the frequency and duration of such contravention or non-compliance;`
  line
  line `(c) the vulnerability of the class of persons likely to be adversely affected by such contravention`
  line `or non-compliance;`
  line
  line `(d) the damage caused or likely to be caused to any person, as a result of such contravention or`
  line `non-compliance, if any;`
  line
  line `(e) the undue gain derived out of such contravention or non-compliance; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other factor, as may be prescribed`
  line
  line `(5) The amount of penalty imposed under the provisions of sections 14A, 14B, 15, 15A or 15B, as the case may be, shall be in addition to the liability to pay relief or compensation under section 15 read with section 17 of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010).]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_d:
  sectionId (89177)
  sectionNo 15D
  orderNo 22
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 15 to 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89177&sectionno=15D&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_15_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[15D. Appeal--(1) Whoever aggrieved by the order, passed by the adjudicating officer under this Act may prefer an appeal to the National Green Tribunal established under section 3 of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010 (19 of 2010).`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within sixty days from the date on which the`
  line `copy of the order made by the adjudicating officer is received by the aggrieved person.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal may, after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such`
  line `order as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an appeal is preferred against any order of the adjudicating officer under sub-section (1),`
  line `such appeal shall not be entertained by the Tribunal unless such person has deposited with the Tribunal`
  line `ten per cent. of the amount of the penalty imposed by the adjudicating officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_e:
  sectionId (89178)
  sectionNo 15E
  orderNo 23
  title `Penalty amount to be credited to Environmental Protection Fund`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_e_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 15 to 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89178&sectionno=15E&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_15_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[15E. Penalty amount to be credited to Environmental Protection Fund.--Where any penalty or`
  line `additional penalty, as the case may be, is imposed under sections 14A, 14B, 15, 15A or section 15B, the`
  line `amount of the penalty shall be credited to the Environmental Protection Fund established under section 16.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_f:
  sectionId (89179)
  sectionNo 15F
  orderNo 24
  title `Offence for failure to pay penalty or additional penalty`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_f_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for sections 15 to 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89179&sectionno=15F&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_15_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[15F. Offence for failure to pay penalty or additional penalty.--(1) Where any person fails to pay the penalty or additional penalty, as the case may be, under sections 14A, 14B, 15, 15A or section 15B within ninety days of such imposition, he shall be liable for imprisonment which may extend to three years or with fine which may extend to twice the amount of the penalty or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any offence under sub-section (1) has been committed by a company, every person who, at`
  line `the time the offence was committed, was directly in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for`
  line `the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `offence and he shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any person liable to any punishment`
  line `provided in sub-section (1), if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), where an offence has been committed by a`
  line `company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance of, or is`
  line `attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company,`
  line `such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and`
  line `shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" includes body corporate, firm, trust, society and any other association of individuals;`
  line
  line `(b) "director" includes director of the company, partner of the firm, members of the society or trust or`
  line `member of any association of individuals, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3967)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 25
  title `Environmental Protection Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3967&sectionno=16&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[CHAPTER IIIA`
  line
  line `FUND, ACCOUNTS AND AUDIT`
  line
  line `16. Environmental Protection Fund.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish a fund to be known as the Environmental Protection Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be credited to the Fund`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of penalty imposed under the Air (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1981 (14 of 1981), and under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the interest or other income received out of investments made from the Fund; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other amount from such sources, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund shall be applied for--`
  line
  line `(a) the promotion of awareness, education and research for the protection of environment;`
  line
  line `(b) the expenses for achieving the objects and for purposes of the Air (Prevention and Control of`
  line `Pollution) Act, 1981(14 of 1981) and under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) such other purposes, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall notify the administrator for the administration of the Fund and other matters connected therewith and incidental thereto in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall allocate seventy-five per cent. of the amount of penalties to the`
  line `State Governments or Union territory administrations, which has been credited to the Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (89180)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 26
  title `Accounts and audit of Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89180&sectionno=16A&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[16A. Accounts and audit of Fund.--(1) The Central Government shall maintain separate accounts and other relevant records in relation to the Environmental Protection Fund and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form, as may be prescribed, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Fund shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at such intervals as may be specified by him and such audited accounts together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded annually to the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_b:
  sectionId (89181)
  sectionNo 16B
  orderNo 27
  title `Annual report.`
  content `^1[16B. Annual report.--The Central Government shall prepare its annual report in relation to Environmental Protection Fund giving a full account of its activities defined under this Act in such form, as may be prescribed, for each financial year during the previous financial year, and shall be laid before each House of Parliament along with audit report given by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.]`
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=89181&sectionno=16B&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3968)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 28
  title `Offences by Government Departments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3968&sectionno=17&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by any Department of Government, the Head of the Department shall be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall render such Head of the Department liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Department of Government and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any officer, other than the Head`
  line `of the Department, such officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (3969)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3969&sectionno=18&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government or any officer or other employee of the Government or any authority`
  line `constituted under this Act or any member, officer or other employee of such authority in respect of`
  line `anything which is done or intended to be done in good faith in pursuance of this Act or the rules made or`
  line `orders or directions issued thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (3970)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 30
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3970&sectionno=19&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act except on`
  line `a complaint made by,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government or any authority or officer authorised in this behalf by that`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) adjudicating officer or any officer authorised by him in this behalf;]`
  line
  line `(b) any person who has given notice of not less than sixty days, in the manner prescribed, of the alleged offence and of his intention to make a complaint, to the Central Government or the authority or officer authorised as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (3971)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 31
  title `Information, reports or returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3971&sectionno=20&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, in relation to its functions`
  line `under this Act, from time to time, require any person, officer, State Government or other authority to`
  line `furnish to it or any prescribed authority or officer any reports, returns, statistics, accounts and other`
  line `information and such person, officer, State Government or other authority shall be bound to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (3972)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 32
  title `Members, officers and employees of the authority constituted under Section 3 to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3972&sectionno=21&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `All the members of the authority, constituted, if any, under section 3 and all officers and other`
  line `employees of such authority when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules made or orders or directions issued thereunder shall be deemed to be public servants within the`
  line `meaning of Section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (3973)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 33
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3973&sectionno=22&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or proceeding in`
  line `respect of anything done, action taken or order or direction issued by the Central Government or any`
  line `other authority or officer in pursuance of any power conferred by or in relation to its or his functions`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (3974)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3974&sectionno=23&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 3, the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, delegate, subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations as may be specified in the notification, such of its powers and functions under this Act [except`
  line `the power to constitute an authority under sub-section (3) of section 3 and to make rules under section 25]`
  line `as it may deem necessary or expedient, to any officer, State Government or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (3975)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 35
  title `Effect of other laws.`
  content `^1[24. Effect of other laws.--The provisions of this Act and the rules or orders made thereunder shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force.]`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule, for section 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3975&sectionno=24&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (3976)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3976&sectionno=25&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the standards in excess of which environmental pollutants shall not be discharged or emitted`
  line `under section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure in accordance with and the safeguards in compliance with which hazardous`
  line `substances shall be handled or cause to be handled under section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the authorities or agencies to which intimation of the fact of occurrence or apprehension of`
  line `occurrence of the discharge of any environmental pollutant in excess of the prescribed standards shall`
  line `be given and to whom all assistance shall be bound to be rendered under sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which samples of air, water, soil or other substance for the purpose of analysis`
  line `shall be taken under sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which notice of intention to have a sample analysed shall be served under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) the functions of the environmental laboratories, the procedure for the submission to such`
  line `laboratories of samples of air, water, soil and other substances for analysis or test; the form of`
  line `laboratory report; the fees payable for such report and other matters to enable such laboratories to`
  line `carry out their functions under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(g) the qualifications of Government Analyst appointed or recognised for the purpose of analysis`
  line `of samples of air, water, soil or other substances under section 13;`
  line
  line `^1[(ga) the manner of holding inquiry and imposing penalty by the adjudicating officer under sub-section (1) and other factors for determining quantum of penalty under clause (f) of sub-section (4) of section 15C;`
  line
  line `(gb) the other amount under clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(gc) the other purposes under clause (c) of sub-section (3) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(gd) the manner of administration of Fund under sub-section (4) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(ge) form for maintenance of accounts of the Fund and for preparation of annual statement of`
  line `accounts under sub-section (1) of section 16A;`
  line
  line `(gf) form for preparing annual report of the Fund under section 16B;]`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which notice of the offence and of the intention to make a complaint to the`
  line `Central Government shall be given under clause (b) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(i) the authority or officer to whom any reports, returns, statistics accounts and other information`
  line `shall be furnished under section 20;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (3977)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 37
  title `Rules made under this Act to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582&sectionId=3977&sectionno=26&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00011_198629_1517807327582
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session,`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that`
  line `the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
